#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:51
#, no-c-format
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr "Indledning"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:53
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kmouth; is a program that enables persons that cannot speak to let their "
"computers speak. It includes a history of spoken sentences from which the "
"user can select sentences to be re-spoken."
msgstr ""
"&kmouth; er et program der gør mennesker der ikke kan tale i stand til at "
"lade deres computere tale. Det inkluderer en historik af udtalte sætninger "
"fra hvilke brugeren kan vælge sætninger til at blive udtalt."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:58
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Note that &kmouth; does not include any speech synthesizers. Instead it "
"requires a speech synthesizer installed in the system."
msgstr ""
"Bemærk at &kmouth; ikke inkluderer nogen tale-synthesizere. I stedet kræver "
"den at der er en tale-synthesizer installeret på systemet."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:65
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using &kmouth;"
msgstr "Brug af &kmouth;"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:67
#, no-c-format
msgid "The First Time Setup"
msgstr "Den første opsætning"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:68
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"During the first use of &kmouth;, a wizard is displayed in which you can "
"configure it."
msgstr ""
"Når &kmouth; startes første gang vil en guide blive vist i hvilken du kan "
"konfigurere den."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:74
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>Text-to-Speech Configuration</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>Tekst-til-tale-konfiguration</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:80
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>Text-to-Speech Configuration</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Tekst-til-tale-konfiguration</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:85
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "With the first page of the wizard you specify the command that shall be "
#| "used for the text-to-speech conversion. For more details look into the "
#| "<link linkend=\"tts-config\">description of the configuration dialog.</"
#| "link>"
msgid ""
"With the first page of the wizard you specify the engine and voice that "
"shall be used for the text-to-speech conversion. For more details look into "
"the <link linkend=\"tts-config\">description of the configuration dialog.</"
"link>"
msgstr ""
"På den første side i guiden angiver du den kommando der vil blive brugt til "
"tekst-til-tale konvertering. For flere detaljer kig i <link linkend=\"tts-"
"config\">beskrivelse af indstillingsdialogen</link>."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:93
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>Word Completion</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>Ordkomplettering</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:99
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>Word Completion</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Ordkomplettering</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:104
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"With the third page you define the dictionary for a word completion. "
"&kmouth; will parse the &kde; documentation of the chosen language in order "
"to detect the regularity of individual words. Optionally you can compare the "
"word list to an OpenOffice.org dictionary in order to only add correctly "
"spelled words to the word completion."
msgstr ""
"Med den tredje side definere du ordbogen for en ordkomplettering. &kmouth; "
"vil gennemgå  &kde;'s dokumentation for det valgte sprog for at detektere "
"hyppigheden af individuelle ord. Derudover kan du vælge at sammenligne "
"ordlisten med en OpenOffice.org-ordbog for at kunne tilføje korrekt stavede "
"ord til ordkompletteringen."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:114
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Main Window"
msgstr "Hovedvinduet"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:115
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The main window of &kmouth; is fairly simple. It consists basically of an "
"edit field into which you type your sentences (the lower white field in the "
"screen shot) and a history of spoken sentences (the upper white field in the "
"screen shot)."
msgstr ""
"Hovedvinduet for &kmouth; er ret simpelt. Det består basalt set af et "
"redigeringsfelt i hvilket du skriver dine sætninger (det nederste hvide felt "
"i skærmbilledet) og en historik af udtalte sætninger (det øverste hvide felt "
"i skærmbilledet)."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:123
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>The main window of &kmouth;</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>&kmouth;'s hovedvindu</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:129
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>The main window of &kmouth;</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>&kmouth;'s hovedvindue</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:134
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Assuming that you have correctly <link linkend=\"config-dialog\">configured "
"&kmouth;</link> you can use the edit field for entering sentences you want "
"to hear. Once a sentence got spoken it will be appended to the history. From "
"the history you can select sentences to be re-spoken."
msgstr ""
"Hvis vi antager at du har <link linkend=\"config-dialog\">indstillet &kmouth;"
"</link> rigtigt, så du kan bruge redigeringsfeltet til at indtaste de "
"sætninger du ønsker at høre. Så vil en sætning der er blevet udtalt blive "
"tilføjet til historikken. Fra historikken kan du så vælge sætninger der skal "
"udtales igen."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:140
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"From the phrase books (located in the line below the tool bar) you can "
"select often used phrases."
msgstr ""
"Fra udtryksbøgerne (der findes i linjen under værktøjslinjen) kan du vælge "
"ofte brugte udtryk."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:146
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Configuration Dialog"
msgstr "Indstillingsdialogen"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:147
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "By using the menu entry <menuchoice> <guimenu>Settings</"
#| "guimenu><guimenuitem>Configure &kmouth;...</guimenuitem> </menuchoice> "
#| "you open the configuration dialog of &kmouth;. This dialog consists of "
#| "the pages <guilabel>General Options</guilabel> with the two tabs "
#| "<guilabel>Preferences</guilabel> and <guilabel>Text-to-Speech</guilabel>, "
#| "the page <guilabel>Word Completion</guilabel> and the page "
#| "<guilabel>Jovie Speech Service</guilabel>."
msgid ""
"By using the menu entry <menuchoice> <guimenu>Settings</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Configure &kmouth;...</guimenuitem> </menuchoice> you "
"open the configuration dialog of &kmouth;. This dialog consists of the pages "
"<guilabel>General Options</guilabel> with the two tabs "
"<guilabel>Preferences</guilabel> and <guilabel>Text-to-Speech</guilabel> and "
"the page <guilabel>Word Completion</guilabel>."
msgstr ""
"Ved at bruge menuindgangen <menuchoice> <guimenu>Opsætning</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Indstil &kmouth;...</guimenuitem> </menuchoice> åbner "
"du &kmouth;'s indstillingsdialog. Denne dialog består af  siderne "
"<guilabel>Generelle indstillinger</guilabel> med de to faneblade "
"<guilabel>Indstillinger</guilabel> og <guilabel>Tekst-til-Tale</guilabel>, "
"siden <guilabel>Ordkomplettering</guilabel> og siden <guilabel>Jovie Tale-"
"tjeneste</guilabel>"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:157
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Preferences tab"
msgstr "Indstillinger-fanebladet"

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:160
#, no-c-format
msgid "The <guilabel>Preferences</guilabel> tab"
msgstr "<guilabel>Indstillinger</guilabel>-fanebladet"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:166 index.docbook:212 index.docbook:289
#, no-c-format
msgid "Screen shot"
msgstr "Skærmbillede"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:171
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <guilabel>Preferences</guilabel> tab contains options that alter the "
"behavior of &kmouth; in certain situations."
msgstr ""
"<guilabel>Indstillinger</guilabel>-fanebladet indeholder tilvalg der ændrer "
"&kmouth;'s opførsel i visse situationer."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:175
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "With the first combo box, <guilabel>Selection of phrases in the phrase "
#| "book:</guilabel>, you specify which action is triggered by typing the "
#| "shortcut of a phrase or by selecting a phrase in the <guimenu>Phrase "
#| "Book</guimenu> menu or in the phrase book bar."
msgid ""
"With the first combo box <guilabel>Selection of phrases in the phrase book</"
"guilabel> you specify which action is triggered by typing the shortcut of a "
"phrase or by selecting a phrase in the <guimenu>Phrase Book</guimenu> menu "
"or in the phrase book bar."
msgstr ""
"Med det første kombinationsfelt, <guilabel>Valg af udtryk i udtryksbogen:</"
"guilabel>, angiver du hvilken handling der udløses ved at skrive genvejen "
"for et udtryk eller ved at vælge udtrykket i <guimenu>Udtryksbog</guimenu>-"
"menuen eller i udtryksbogslinjen."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:181
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"By selecting <guilabel>Speak Immediately</guilabel> the selected phrase gets "
"immediately spoken and is entered into the history. If you select "
"<guilabel>Insert Into Edit Field</guilabel> the selected phrase is just "
"inserted into the edit field."
msgstr ""
"Ved at vælge <guilabel>Tal med det samme</guilabel> vil det valgte udtryk "
"blive udtalt med det samme og indgår i historikken. Hvis du vælger "
"<guilabel>Indsæt i redigeringsfelt</guilabel> bliver det valgte udtryk blot "
"indsat i redigeringsfeltet."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:188
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "With the second combo box, <guilabel>Closing the phrase book edit window:"
#| "</guilabel>, you specify whether the phrase book gets saved if you just "
#| "close the phrase book edit window."
msgid ""
"With the second combo box, <guilabel>Closing the phrase book edit window</"
"guilabel>, you specify whether the phrase book gets saved if you just close "
"the phrase book edit window."
msgstr ""
"Med det andet kombinationsfelt, <guilabel>Lukker udtryksbogens "
"redigeringsvindue:</guilabel>, angiver du om udtryksbogen bliver gemt hvis "
"du blot lukker udtryksbogens redigeringsvindue."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:193
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"By selecting <guilabel>Save Phrase Book</guilabel> the phrase book gets "
"saved. If you select <guilabel>Discard changes</guilabel> the changes are "
"discarded and the phrase book is not saved. If you select <guilabel>Ask "
"Whether to Save</guilabel> &kmouth; will ask you whether it shall save the "
"phrase book."
msgstr ""
"Ved at vælge <guilabel>Gem udtryksbog</guilabel> bliver udtryksbogen gemt. "
"Hvis du vælger <guilabel>Kassér ændringer</guilabel> bliver ændringerne "
"kasserede og udtryksbogen bliver ikke gemt. Hvis du vælger <guilabel>Spørg "
"om der skal gemmes</guilabel> vil &kmouth; spørge dig om den skal gemme "
"udtryksbogen."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:203
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Text-to-Speech tab"
msgstr "Tekst-til-tale-fanebladet"

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:206
#, no-c-format
msgid "The <guilabel>Text-to-Speech</guilabel> tab"
msgstr "<guilabel>Tekst-til-tale</guilabel>-fanebladet"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:217
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "By selecting <guilabel>Use Jovie speech service if possible</guilabel> "
#| "you tell &kmouth; first to try to send the text to the Jovie speech "
#| "service. If this succeeds the other configuration entries on this tab are "
#| "ignored. The Jovie speech service is a &kde; daemon which gives &kde; "
#| "applications a standardized interface for speech synthesis and is "
#| "currently developed in <acronym>Git</acronym>. It is safe to select this "
#| "option even if Jovie is not installed."
msgid ""
"By selecting <guilabel>Use default speech system</guilabel> you tell "
"&kmouth; first to try to use the system speech service prior to calling the "
"speech synthesizer directly. If this succeeds the other configuration "
"entries on this tab are ignored. The system speech service is a &Qt; library "
"which wraps speech-dispatcher on &Linux;, and native speech systems on other "
"platforms. On a Debian based system you need the packages speech-dispatcher, "
"libqt5texttospeech5 and one of the speech-dispatcher modules, usually "
"<application>espeak</application>."
msgstr ""
"Ved at vælge <guilabel>Brug Jovie taletjeneste om muligt</guilabel> beder du "
"&kmouth; om først at prøve at sende teksten til Jovie taletjenesten. Hvis "
"det lykkes bliver de andre indgange i indstillingen i dette faneblad "
"ignoreret. Jovie taletjenesten er en &kde;-dæmon som giver &kde;-programmer "
"en standardiseret grænseflade til talesyntese og for øjeblikket udvikles i "
"<acronym>Git</acronym>. Det er sikkert at vælge dette selvom Jovie ikke er "
"installeret."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:225
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use the commandline tool <command>spd-conf</command> (Debian package python3-"
"speechd) to adjust settings like rate, pitch, volume, voice type and "
"language &etc; for the default speech system. Additionally <command>spd-"
"conf</command> will let you choose between all installed speech-dispatcher "
"modules, &ie; <application>espeak</application>, <application>festival</"
"application>, <application>flite</application>, <application>mbrola</"
"application> &etc;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:233
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It is also possible to select the <guilabel>Engine</guilabel> and "
"<guilabel>Voice</guilabel> for the speech system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:236
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Into the edit field of the <guilabel>Text-to-Speech</guilabel> tab you "
#| "enter the command for calling the speech synthesizer. With the combo box "
#| "below the edit field you specify the character encoding that is used for "
#| "passing the text to the speech synthesizer."
msgid ""
"Should the <guilabel>Use default speech system</guilabel> item is not "
"selected you can enter the command for calling the speech synthesize into "
"the edit field of the <guilabel>Alternative</guilabel> panel. With the combo "
"box below the edit field you specify the character encoding that is used for "
"passing the text to the speech synthesizer."
msgstr ""
"I redigeringsfeltet i <guilabel>Tekst-til-tale</guilabel>-fanebladet "
"indtaster du kommandoen der kalder en tale-synthesizer. Med "
"kombinationsboksen under redigeringsfeltet angiver du det tegnsæt der bliver "
"brugt til at videregive tekst til tale-synthesizer."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:242
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kmouth; knows two ways of passing the text: If the command expects the text "
"as standard input you select the check box."
msgstr ""
"&kmouth; kender til to måder at videregive teksten: Hvis kommandoen "
"forventer tekst som standard inddata markerer du afkrydsningsfeltet."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:246
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The other way is to pass the text as a parameter: Before calling the command "
"&kmouth; replaces certain placeholders with actual content:"
msgstr ""
"Den anden måde er at videregive teksten som en parameter: Før kommandoen "
"&kmouth; kaldes, erstattes visse pladsholdere med faktisk indhold:"

#. Tag: entry
